messages.messageBody:
6/14/03 01:56:

> We got a house! I'm SO happy and excited!!!

Congrats, Jennifer!
>
> And nervous...we have 10 days to move and I haven't packed a thing, save
> three boxes of books. AAAAHHH!

You can do it! One box at a time. Books are a great place to start, you
won't have time to read for the next few weeks anyway! Recruit your kids to
pack unbreakables. They may not be packed the way you'd do it, but they'll
be packed! My son also loved taping boxes together.
>
> Add that to the fact that I'm packing and moving alone...my husband
> conveniently doesn't get home until the day AFTER we have to be out of this
> house...and I'm a nervous wreck!

Oh, yuck. I still know you can do it. I did our last move alone, and it
sucked, but it's done! Hang in there!

brenda
